## 10. Which layers are these in?

Layer of a hex (q,r,s) = max(|q|,|r|,|s|).

Our point: max(26,4,22)=26 → layer26.

Check neighbors:

E: (-25,4,21) max(25,4,21)=25 → layer25.  
NE: (-25,3,22) max(25,3,22)=25 → layer25.  
NW: (-26,3,23) max(26,3,23)=26 → layer26.  
W: (-27,4,23) max(27,4,23)=27 → layer27.  
SW: (-27,5,22) max(27,5,22)=27 → layer27.  
SE: (-26,5,21) max(26,5,21)=26 → layer26.

So neighbors: 2 in layer25, 2 in layer27, 2 in layer26.

